commitResults.messageTitle: Added the driver function to take in user input. Added ArrayList to store input.
Level 2
Updated to level 3.
Level-4 Improved layout of code. Added children classes for task to give more granularity to the different types of tasks.
Level-5 Added try-catch blocks to flag errors, and prevent possible incorrect input from created unwanted stops/breakages in the program.
Level-6 Added the removeTask method for deletion
Renamed to Duke.java
Level-7 Added I/O utility. Autocreate data directory if it does not exist.
Level-8 Added date time formatter across all task classes. Created a ParseDate class to handle date formatting.
A-J-Unit Add-gradle-support Included J-unit tests under dependencies in build.gradle file Added gradle wrapper files as well
Level-9 Added a find function uitlity to filter tasks by keyword
A-MoreOOP Refactored a bulk of the code from Duke.java into four classes: Parser, Storage, TaskList, and Ui. Modified Duke.java to accomodate these changes as well.

Add JUnit Tests Included the gradle wrapper and the associated dependencies for the Junit test. Added two JUnit Test: One to test the loading of the stored text file, the other to test marking as done utility. Both under src/test/java.
Made the classes more OOP-like. Applied changes to all other dependent classes as well.
Level-10 Added GUI and modified the corresponding methods to return a string (rather than stdout) to feed into the user input functions, which are returned and displayed in the dialogue box in GUI.
Added important assertions throughout the code. Some of them include checks for non empty objects, and list to avoid unchecked null pointers which can crash the program.
Improved abstration in the Duke.java, erasing direct array/list access as much as possible by abstracting it away into the Task classes.
Improved the find function to be more flexible, giving the user the option to specify type of search: partial case sensitive, partial non- case sensitive, full exact match.
Built a basic GUI for interaction betwen user and bot. GUI echoes user commands, returns output by bot.
Added a simple user guide with some usage examples and corresponding output
Added java doc comments for most methods, less the getter and setter methods which are quite clear.

Improved code quality by ensuring similar levels of abstraction in a method body. Prevented as much as possible the use of magic strings when it comes to important kinds of data. Avoided direct usage of list indexing in Duke method by abstracting to the TaskList method.
Refactored CLI version of Duke.java.
Improved consistency of String representation and formatting.
Added input and expected text to the files. Debugged some of the inconsistencies for specific inputs like missing spaces.
Fixed launching issues with duke.jar file.
Made final changes to the readMe file and added a background image.
Update README.md
Delete README.md
Updated minor changes to UI class.
